ZH:我不同意你的偏见。
EN:I don't agree with your prejudice.

ZH:他对外国人有很多偏见。
EN:He has a lot of prejudice against foreigners.

ZH:不要因为她的外表而有偏见。
EN:Don't judge her based on her appearance.

ZH:这是一种常见的偏见。
EN:This is a common prejudice.

ZH:她说话的方式带有很明显的偏见。
EN:She speaks in a way that is clearly biased.

ZH:我们必须消除种族偏见。
EN:We must eliminate racial prejudice.

ZH:她受到了性别偏见的待遇。
EN:She has experienced gender bias.

ZH:学校应该教育学生避免偏见。
EN:Schools should educate students to avoid prejudice.

ZH:这本书试图打破人们的偏见。
EN:This book attempts to challenge people's prejudices.

ZH:我希望这个世界能摆脱偏见。
EN:I hope this world can be free from prejudice.

ZH:我并不是有意带有偏见。
EN:I don't intend to be prejudiced.

ZH:请不要让你的偏见影响你的判断。
EN:Please don't let your prejudice cloud your judgment.

ZH:这种言论带有很大的偏见。
EN:This statement is highly biased.

ZH:我们应该努力消除社会上的偏见。
EN:We should strive to eradicate prejudice in society.

ZH:他在招聘过程中没有偏见。
EN:He has no bias in the recruitment process.

ZH:别因为他的背景而有偏见。
EN:Don't judge him based on his background.

ZH:这种态度充满了偏见。
EN:This attitude is filled with prejudice.

ZH:我们不能因为种族而有偏见。
EN:We must not be prejudiced based on race.

ZH:我的观点并不是出于偏见。
EN:My viewpoint is not based on prejudice.

ZH:有些人对外国文化怀有偏见。
EN:Some people have prejudices against foreign cultures.
